Package: iLBA
Title: Information Loss Bounded Aggregation
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jeehyun", "Hwang", email = "hwangjh@snu.ac.kr", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Dongsun", "Yoon", email = "dsyoon@umich.edu", role = "aut")
  )
Description: Provides tools for constructing confidential frequency tables
    from a microdata set with hierarchical variables using the iLBA algorithm. 
    As the demand for aggregated frequency tables defined on selected subsets 
    of variables increases, the iLBA algorithm offers an effective masking 
    approach. It enables the confidential release of such tables by jointly 
    controlling disclosure risk and information loss. The package supports the
    generation of masked finest-level frequency tables, masked aggregated 
    frequency tables, and masked counts for individual cells in aggregated tables.
